            <li><strong>Not Thread-Safe in All Environments:</strong> While JavaScript is single-threaded, in more complex setups (e.g., with web workers), Singletons can introduce race conditions if not handled carefully.</li>
            <li><strong>Difficulty in Extension:</strong> If you need multiple instances (e.g., different themes per user session), the pattern makes it hard to adapt without refactoring.</li>
