        <p>This version allows multiple tasks to update the shared progress state simultaneously without synchronization. In a multi-threaded environment, this could lead to race conditions, resulting in incorrect progress values (e.g., lost updates). In JavaScript, the single-threaded event loop masks the issue somewhat, but it's still illustrative of real-world problems.</p>
